	<td align="right" width="40%"><font face="univers,arial,sans-serif" color="#ffffff"><b>using</b></font></td>

	<td width="1%" align="center"><font face="univers,arial,sans-serif" color="#ffffff"><b>|</b></font></td>

	<td width="59%" <font face="univers,arial,sans-serif">The
	installation procedures have change from the previous
	version. You need an installed version of SWIG1.1p5 (i.e. you
	need libswig.a and swig.h) These are the steps to build SWIGLua:
	</font>
	  <ul>
	    <li><font face="univers,arial,sans-serif"><tt>tar xvfz
	    SWIGLua-0.3.tar.gz</tt></font></li>
	    <li><font face="univers,arial,sans-serif"><tt>make; make install</tt></font></li>
	  </ul>
	</td>
      </tr>
